               <p>MR. EDWARD BURMESTER. I live in St. Helen's-place. On the 13th of August, at four o'clock in the afternoon, I was coming from <placeName id="t18280911-7-crimeloc35">America-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-7-crimeloc35" type="placeName" value="America-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-7-crimeloc35" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-7-off33 t18280911-7-crimeloc35"></join> towards <placeName id="t18280911-7-crimeloc36">Crutchedfriars</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-7-crimeloc36" type="placeName" value="Crutchedfriars"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-7-crimeloc36" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-7-off33 t18280911-7-crimeloc36"></join> with a gentlemen, and telling him of having lost a handkerchief a week before; I felt a touch at my pocket and said "I have lost another" - I turned round and saw the prisoner throw it from his hand - he was a very few paces off; I charged him with it instantly, and secured him; he tried to run away - I saw it fall from his hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-7-person140">
                  THOMAS 
                  DEVEY
               <interp inst="t18280911-7-person140" type="surname" value="DEVEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-7-person140" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-7-person140" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and took the prisoner in charge with the handkerchief.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was about one hundred yards from the gentlemen - it rained; a gentlemen took hold of me and took me into a shop; this gentleman came up and said, "My lad, you avnd another one have taken my handkerchief."</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-7-verdict37" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-7-verdict37" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 16.</p>
